        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 6:07PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 607 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles north of Washburn, or 15 miles west of Panhandle. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pantex.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
